Questions I can now answer
  1. What Collegiate Volleyball team is ranked the highest?
  2. What is cache?
  3. Who are the representatives from Massachusetts?
  4. What is Hypertext Markup Language?
  5. What are the top 25 Law Schools in the U.S?
  1. What Collegiate Volleyball has won the most championships?
    My answer is... I found this under the file NCAA Men's Champions-Division One. volley This file gives you a listing of the champions back to the year 1970. Last year the champion was Penn State, and the runner up was UCLA. The team that won the most championships is UCLA. If one would like to go to look at the various Volleyball teams World Wide, there is the Volleyball World Wide Home Page that has a lot of various information that one could get aquainted with volleyball.

    Return to list of questions.

  2. What is cache?
    My answer is...Cache is a storage system for frequently used infomation. Cache I found a URL that is a cache server as an extension to http-1.1. This URL implements a simple cache server. I also found if the client is configured appropriately the server can act as a cache for WWW requests.store.

    Return to list of questions.

  3. Who are the representatives from Massachusetts?
    My answer is...I found several interesting things in relation to the representatives in Massachusetts. The Representatives are listed by states. There are so many ways to contact the representative of your choice. Click here to see how you can get in touch with a representative from your state. There are House directories and e-mail addresses that you can get a hold of, especially if your representative is not doing their job.

    Return to list of questions.

  4. What is Hypertext Markup Language?
    My answer is...HTML is a markup language for hypertext which is understood by all WWW clients. This defines the levels of standardization of HTML. Located within this is a server guide that HELPS anyone who wants to learn about this system. It is very informative and it is great for beginners.

    Return to list of questions.

  5. What are a few Law Schools in the U.S., and where are they located?
    My answer is...There are several Law Schools in the United States. A few that I found through the WEB are University of Arkansas, University of Cincinnati, College of Law, and The University of Texas at Austin, School of Law. All of these Law Schools have a lot of information on each of their programs which allows the user to become familiar with the school.

    Return to list of questions.
